osed in error messages or logs, attackers could post to the webhook.\",\n      \"category\": \"credential-exposure\",\n      \"cwe\": \"CWE-798: Use of Hard-coded Credentials\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"riskScore\": 28,\n  \"recommendations\": [\n    \"URGENT: Fix notify.py:72 - Replace os.environ['SMTP_PASS'] with os.getenv('SMTP_PASS') to prevent KeyError crashes\",\n    \"URGENT: Add jobs.db to .gitignore - Database contains sensitive job data and should never be in version control\",\n    \"Add secrets protection in GitHub workflow - Prevent environment variable exposure in logs/errors\",\n    \"Validate config file path in cli.py - Restrict --config argument to specific directories\",\n    \"Document Meta GraphQL doc_id rotation process - Currently hardcoded at fetchers.py:865, will break when Meta updates it\",\n    \"Add request signing for webhooks in notify.py - Prevent webhook forgery if URL is exposed\",\n    \"Verify all URLs use HTTPS - Ensure no HTTP fallbacks exist for sensitive requests\",\n    \"Review regex patterns for ReDoS attacks - Check fetchers.py regex patterns if they become dynamic\",\n    \"Add graceful error logging - Log failed notifications without exposing credentials\"\n  ],\n  \"security_strengths\": [\n    \"✓ All secrets loaded from environment variables, not hardcoded\",\n    \"✓ SQL queries use parameterized statements preventing SQL injection\",\n    \"✓ PyYAML.safe_load() used instead of unsafe yaml.load()\",\n    \"✓ Subprocess calls use list form (no shell=True)\",\n    \"✓ HTTPS used for all API endpoints\",\n    \"✓ Request timeouts configured (20s default)\",\n    \"✓ No direct HTML rendering vulnerabilities\",\n    \"✓ User-Agent set for all requests\"\n  ],\n  \"summary\": \"The codebase has strong baseline security with proper parameterized queries and environment variables for secrets. Primary risks are operational: unsafe environment variable access and sensitive data (job listings) committed to git.\",\n  \"riskScore_details\": {\n    \"critical\": 0,\n    \"high\": 0,\n    \"medium\": 1,\n    \"low\": 4,\n    \"informational\": 2\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Key Findings\n\n**Critical Issues:** None identified\n\n**Medium Severity:**\n- **notify.py:72** - Unsafe `os.environ['SMTP_PASS']` access will crash if key missing. Use `os.getenv()` instead.\n\n**Low Severity (But Important):**\n- **jobs.db in git** - Database with all job listings should NOT be committed. Add to .gitignore.\n- **Workflow persists sensitive data** - Database commits create searchable history of job data.\n- **Command construction** - mode_words passed to os.execvp, though relatively safe with list form.\n- **Webhook credential exposure** - Slack webhook in env vars could be logged in errors.\n\n### Strengths\n✅ No hardcoded secrets  \n✅ All SQL queries parameterized  \n✅ Safe YAML parsing (safe_load)  \n✅ No shell injection risks  \n✅ HTTPS for all APIs  \n\n### Next Steps\n1. Add `jobs.db` to `.gitignore` immediately\n2. Fix line 72 in `notify.py` to use `os.getenv()`\n3. Review GitHub secrets handling in workflow logs\n",
